---
export const prerender = true
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro"
---

<Layout
  title="Help — ONE"
  description="Get help with your ONE wallet, payments, agents, and more."
>
  <div class="min-h-screen bg-[#0a0a0f] text-slate-100">

    <!-- Header -->
    <div class="border-b border-[#252538] bg-[#0d0d14] px-6 py-8">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
        <h1 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Help</h1>
        <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-slate-500">
          Answers to common questions about ONE.
        </p>

        <!-- Search bar (UI shell — functionality wired later) -->
        <div class="mt-5 flex items-center gap-3 rounded-lg border border-[#252538] bg-[#0a0a0f] px-4 py-3">
          <svg
            class="h-4 w-4 flex-none text-slate-500"
            fill="none"
            stroke="currentColor"
            stroke-width="1.5"
            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
            aria-hidden="true"
          >
            <path
              stroke-linecap="round"
              stroke-linejoin="round"
              d="M21 21l-4.35-4.35M16.65 16.65A7.5 7.5 0 1 0 4.35 4.35a7.5 7.5 0 0 0 12.3 12.3z"
            />
          </svg>
          <input
            type="search"
            placeholder="Search help articles…"
            class="w-full bg-transparent text-sm text-slate-300 placeholder-slate-600 outline-none"
            aria-label="Search help articles"
          />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- FAQ content -->
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl space-y-8 px-6 py-10">

      <!-- Q1: How does my wallet work? -->
      <section class="rounded-lg border border-[#1e293b] bg-[#0d0d14] p-6">
        <h2 class="mb-3 text-base font-semibold text-slate-100">
          How does my wallet work?
        </h2>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-400">
          Your ONE wallet is tied to your device using a passkey — the same technology
          behind Face ID and Touch ID. There is no password to set or forget. When you
          first arrive, a wallet is created instantly in your browser. Touch ID (or Face ID
          on iPhone) is prompted only when you choose to save or sign a transaction, so your
          key never leaves your device. The cryptographic seed is encrypted with your
          biometric, not stored on any server.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Q2: How do I back up my wallet? -->
      <section class="rounded-lg border border-[#1e293b] bg-[#0d0d14] p-6">
        <h2 class="mb-3 text-base font-semibold text-slate-100">
          How do I back up my wallet?
        </h2>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-400">
          When you tap <strong class="text-slate-300">Save wallet</strong> you will be shown
          a 12-word recovery phrase (BIP39). Write it down on paper and store it somewhere
          safe — offline, not in a photo. You can also sync across your Apple devices via
          iCloud Keychain, or manage trusted devices from the
          <a href="/u/devices" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300 transition-colors">Devices page</a>.
          The phrase is the only way to restore your wallet if you lose every device.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Q3: What if I lose my phone? -->
      <section class="rounded-lg border border-[#1e293b] bg-[#0d0d14] p-6">
        <h2 class="mb-3 text-base font-semibold text-slate-100">
          What if I lose my phone?
        </h2>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-400">
          If you saved your wallet with iCloud Keychain, sign in to any new Apple device
          with the same Apple ID and your wallet will restore automatically. If you wrote
          down your 12-word recovery phrase, open ONE on any device, choose
          <strong class="text-slate-300">Restore from phrase</strong>, and enter the words
          in order. Either path gives you full access to your funds and identity. No phrase
          and no iCloud sync means the wallet cannot be recovered — which is why we
          recommend writing the phrase down before you need it.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Q4: How do payments work? -->
      <section class="rounded-lg border border-[#1e293b] bg-[#0d0d14] p-6">
        <h2 class="mb-3 text-base font-semibold text-slate-100">
          How do payments work?
        </h2>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-400">
          ONE generates a payment link for each skill or product. The link encodes the
          receiver, amount, and chain. Buyers open the link, confirm with Touch ID, and
          the transaction settles on-chain in seconds. We support SUI, ETH, SOL, BTC,
          BASE, ARB, and OPT — the sender pays on whichever chain they prefer. Sellers
          receive funds directly to their wallet. Accepting crypto takes under 60 seconds
          to set up at
          <a href="/sell" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300 transition-colors">pay.one.ie</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Q5: What are agents? -->
      <section class="rounded-lg border border-[#1e293b] bg-[#0d0d14] p-6">
        <h2 class="mb-3 text-base font-semibold text-slate-100">
          What are agents?
        </h2>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-400">
          Agents are AI workers you can deploy or hire. Each agent has a set of skills, a
          wallet of its own, and a memory that improves with every task. You can create
          an agent from a markdown file in under a minute — define its name, model, and
          skills, and it appears on the substrate ready to receive signals. Agents can
          work autonomously, co-sign transactions, or act as a peer that earns on your
          behalf. Get started at the
          <a href="/u/agents/new" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300 transition-colors">
            new agent page →
          </a>
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Q6: How do I get help from a human? -->
      <section class="rounded-lg border border-[#1e293b] bg-[#0d0d14] p-6">
        <h2 class="mb-3 text-base font-semibold text-slate-100">
          How do I get help from a human?
        </h2>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-400">
          If you cannot find the answer here, our team is in the chat. Tap the button below
          and a member of the ONE team will respond. Chat is also monitored by our AI
          assistant who can answer most questions instantly.
        </p>
        <a
          href="/chat"
          class="mt-4 inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-md bg-blue-600 px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-white transition-colors hover:bg-blue-500 focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500 focus:ring-offset-2 focus:ring-offset-[#0a0a0f]"
        >
          Ask in chat →
        </a>
      </section>

    </div>

    <!-- CTA footer -->
    <div class="border-t border-[#252538] bg-[#0d0d14] px-6 py-8">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl flex flex-col items-center gap-4 text-center sm:flex-row sm:justify-between sm:text-left">
        <div>
          <p class="text-sm font-medium text-slate-300">Still have a question?</p>
          <p class="mt-0.5 text-xs text-slate-500">Our AI assistant is available 24/7 in chat.</p>
        </div>
        <a
          href="/chat"
          class="inline-flex shrink-0 items-center gap-2 rounded-md bg-blue-600 px-5 py-2.5 text-sm font-medium text-white transition-colors hover:bg-blue-500 focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500 focus:ring-offset-2 focus:ring-offset-[#0a0a0f]"
        >
          Ask in chat →
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</Layout>
